WEBVTT

00:32.490 --> 00:35.994
Uber owns no vehicles.
    Facebook creates no content.

00:36.036 --> 00:37.746
Alibaba has no inventory.

00:37.746 --> 00:40.957
The world is shifting from
           tangible assets

00:40.999 --> 00:42.167
to digital convenience.

00:42.167 --> 00:46.379
That is why I'm here presenting
   this idea to the panel, today.

00:46.421 --> 00:48.006
We've developed an app to bring

00:48.006 --> 00:50.425
the $10 trillion
         derivative industry

00:50.467 --> 00:52.635
to the blockchain
          by the year 2018,

00:52.635 --> 00:55.430
with our half percent fee
        charged on collateral

00:55.472 --> 00:58.058
deposited in
        our smart contracts.

00:58.058 --> 01:00.560
May I ask you to pause it
            for a second?

01:00.602 --> 01:03.688
So using your app,
       I take my 100 Bitcoins

01:03.688 --> 01:06.274
-and pretend it's Apple shares?
                -Yes.

01:06.274 --> 01:07.942
So, it's a bit like in trade.

01:07.942 --> 01:11.821
Yeah, you're planning to launch
     other asset classes, yeah?

01:11.821 --> 01:14.240
I guess it wasn't clear
        from my presentation.

01:14.282 --> 01:16.868
Well, we're Book Club,
          We like clarity.

01:16.868 --> 01:18.119
This isn't Y Combinator.

01:18.119 --> 01:20.121
We've created the framework
          for someone else

01:20.121 --> 01:21.456
-to create digital assets--
          -No. I got that.

01:21.498 --> 01:24.042
-So it won't be our problem.
   -Well, it will be your problem.

01:24.042 --> 01:26.586
Because to the SEC
           or to the CSDC,

01:26.586 --> 01:28.713
it's gonna look like
         a brokerage trade.

01:28.713 --> 01:30.757
Which exemptions
         do you plan to use?

01:36.137 --> 01:38.181
I don't have the answer
         to that right now.

01:38.181 --> 01:40.475
I won't pretend to have
      the answer when I don't.

01:40.475 --> 01:44.145
All right. Well, "right now"
     doesn't exist in a vacuum.

01:44.145 --> 01:46.189
So, why don't you
     think about what I've said

01:46.189 --> 01:48.775
and come back in a year,
      'cause it's a great idea?

01:48.775 --> 01:50.860
Excuse me, sir.
        Ms. Flood is outside.

01:50.860 --> 01:53.488
What do you mean she's
    outside? Why isn't she here?

01:54.489 --> 01:56.491
Uh, if you could excuse me.

02:01.579 --> 02:03.540
Hey. Edes, what's up?
            Is it the AC?

02:03.581 --> 02:04.582
I had them turn it off.

02:04.624 --> 02:05.792
We're in puddles
         of sweat in there.

02:05.792 --> 02:09.087
I had to have three
    Kahlua popsicles to cool off.

02:09.087 --> 02:10.630
Why aren't you in there?

02:11.714 --> 02:13.049
What are you
         doing here, Wyant?

02:13.049 --> 02:15.426
Hatch, as I'm sure you're aware,

02:15.468 --> 02:18.263
OriGen doesn't
        require notice for...

02:18.930 --> 02:20.974
Well, for termination.

02:21.015 --> 02:22.058
What are you talking about?

02:22.058 --> 02:23.893
We received confirmation
           45 minutes ago.

02:23.935 --> 02:26.938
-Confirmation of what?
    -That you're a fucking thief.

02:26.938 --> 02:27.647
What?

02:27.689 --> 02:29.774
Thomas Newton's tenth patent

02:29.774 --> 02:32.986
was found on your
         personal computer.

02:33.027 --> 02:34.028
By removing it from OriGen,

02:34.028 --> 02:36.531
you violated your
     non-disclosure agreements.

02:36.531 --> 02:38.825
-We need you to sign, Hatch.
            -No.

02:39.784 --> 02:40.577
Fuck you!

02:40.618 --> 02:43.621
I was doing a 360 risk audit
         of Dad's annuities.

02:43.663 --> 02:46.124
I'm the risk officer.
           That's my job.

02:46.124 --> 02:48.585
Which patent whore
        were you selling to?

02:48.585 --> 02:51.004
-Is it Intel? Apple?
           -Edie, please.

02:51.045 --> 02:53.506
I wasn't stealing anything
   and I wasn't selling anything.

02:53.548 --> 02:55.842
I was trying to understand
         the fucking thing.

02:55.842 --> 02:58.970
Wyant, can you go recharge in
    your flying pod or whatever?

02:59.012 --> 03:00.263
I need to talk to
           my baby sister.

03:00.305 --> 03:03.349
I didn't mean that pejoratively.
    I mean, like a powerful baby.

03:03.349 --> 03:04.976
A baby who can run a company--

03:04.976 --> 03:06.477
You are the infant here.

03:06.519 --> 03:07.854
You are so incompetent.

03:07.896 --> 03:11.024
You disguised the patent on your
    computer as a fucking recipe.

03:11.024 --> 03:13.234
For hummus?
        I'm the vegan, Hatch.

03:13.276 --> 03:14.485
You eat cigarettes
          wrapped in shit!

03:14.527 --> 03:16.988
Whatever contracts Dad inherited
      when he took over OriGen

03:17.030 --> 03:19.032
have left us with
          massive exposure.

03:19.073 --> 03:20.200
It's even more insulting
           that you think

03:20.241 --> 03:21.576
you can distract me
         with this bullshit.

03:21.576 --> 03:23.411
Did you know that
    that patent was classified as

03:23.411 --> 03:25.163
top secret by the US
        Department of Energy?

03:25.205 --> 03:26.748
Which is fucking terrifying?

03:26.748 --> 03:28.333
You didn't. And neither did I.

03:28.374 --> 03:30.043
Because Dad didn't
         see fit to tell us

03:30.043 --> 03:31.419
before he jumped off a cliff.

03:31.419 --> 03:32.545
Why would he tell you anything

03:32.545 --> 03:34.005
given how little
       he thought of you, huh?

03:34.047 --> 03:36.633
You somehow managed to be
     roiling in contempt for him

03:36.674 --> 03:38.051
while drowning in Kahlua.

03:38.092 --> 03:39.302
Kahlua, in the 21st century.

03:39.302 --> 03:41.888
You've never been able to
       get past that Dad left

03:41.888 --> 03:43.598
controlling interest
       of the company to me--

03:43.640 --> 03:45.850
So that he could control you
           from the grave!

03:45.850 --> 03:47.143
You never wanted
         to see what he was.

03:47.185 --> 03:50.063
-He was a visionary.
      -He wasn't the visionary.

03:50.980 --> 03:51.898
No.

03:51.940 --> 03:52.690
No, no, no.

03:52.690 --> 03:54.192
I am not gonna
          let you make this

03:54.192 --> 03:56.110
about your obsession
          with that freak.

03:56.152 --> 03:57.612
Nobody knows
        what Thomas Newton's

03:57.612 --> 04:00.281
tenth patent was.
     Nobody knows what it does.

04:00.281 --> 04:01.658
Why was it written
             in base 60?

04:01.658 --> 04:03.326
That's not even
         our number system.

04:03.326 --> 04:04.410
It's a word salad.

04:04.410 --> 04:05.828
That's why it's been sitting
      on a shelf for 45 years.

04:05.828 --> 04:08.122
Then why was it classified
   the second that he disappeared?

04:08.164 --> 04:09.874
I'm not engaging in this.
           You're a thief.

04:09.916 --> 04:12.001
-Who fucking cares? Sign.
          -You should care.

04:12.043 --> 04:15.004
Because without Newton's patents
         OriGen is nothing.

04:15.046 --> 04:16.464
His tech was magic.

04:16.464 --> 04:18.424
It was like from another planet.

04:18.466 --> 04:20.343
Another planet? Oh, my God.

04:20.385 --> 04:22.679
Can we please... Can this
      just be about you and me?

04:22.720 --> 04:25.682
I've been killing myself
   holding this company together.

04:25.682 --> 04:28.518
The only way we make money,
    Hatch, is with those patents,

04:28.559 --> 04:30.687
and you tried to go sell one
         to our competition.

04:30.728 --> 04:32.438
It doesn't matter that it's old

04:32.480 --> 04:34.315
and it doesn't matter
         that it's useless.

04:34.315 --> 04:37.860
You did it to fuck me
       because you're jealous!

04:37.902 --> 04:40.154
Because you hate that
           Dad hated you.

04:42.448 --> 04:44.117
Edie...

04:44.158 --> 04:49.163
Dad had a million secrets that
   you never wanted to look into.

04:50.123 --> 04:52.375
This one is dangerous enough

04:52.417 --> 04:54.460
to be squashed
        by the US government.

04:54.460 --> 04:56.671
This conversation's over.
          Sign the papers.

04:56.671 --> 04:58.256
Please, can I...

04:58.298 --> 05:00.758
Can I just say
      "Please, don't fire me?"

05:00.758 --> 05:04.137
Look, OriGen is all that I have.
         It's all that I am.

05:04.137 --> 05:05.763
I love it despite Dad.

05:05.805 --> 05:08.057
I don't know anything else.

05:08.057 --> 05:10.268
I... Look, I can't...

05:10.310 --> 05:11.269
I can't bargain with you.

05:11.269 --> 05:13.354
I can't, um,
       threaten consequences.

05:13.354 --> 05:16.316
I can just say, "Please,
      don't fire your brother."

05:19.610 --> 05:20.987
Sign.

05:22.363 --> 05:24.157
I'm erasing you.

05:37.295 --> 05:38.713
He would've been
          happy about this.

05:38.755 --> 05:40.381
Yeah, he would.

05:48.639 --> 05:49.974
Um...

05:50.350 --> 05:51.392
Edie...

05:52.685 --> 05:55.355
Whatever's
     in that patent, there's...

05:55.396 --> 05:57.857
no way it doesn't come back
            to burn you.

06:21.422 --> 06:26.761
Can we go
           to Seattle now?

06:28.304 --> 06:29.889
Water.

06:29.889 --> 06:32.558
-Water.
     -He hardly weighs a thing.

06:32.558 --> 06:34.227
Water.

06:36.354 --> 06:37.563
Oh, my God.

06:39.357 --> 06:41.526
I need something.
          Come on, come on.

06:44.695 --> 06:45.696
More!

06:45.696 --> 06:47.407
-More.
            -Here. Here.

06:47.407 --> 06:49.909
--Come on.

06:57.458 --> 06:59.919
-Oh, sh...

07:00.753 --> 07:04.048
Oh, my God.
             Oh, my God.

07:14.642 --> 07:16.894
--Oh, my God.

07:44.630 --> 07:46.257
-Oh.

07:47.800 --> 07:50.344
We can go to OriGen now.

07:52.763 --> 07:54.140
Bless you.

07:56.559 --> 07:58.311
God bless you.

08:51.697 --> 08:53.324
I can shave.

09:11.676 --> 09:13.386
Wait.

09:13.427 --> 09:15.930
I... I'm not ready for this.

09:16.764 --> 09:18.933
Don't be afraid, Juzzie.

09:23.521 --> 09:26.065
It's okay. Come on.

09:35.408 --> 09:36.742
Come here.

10:05.521 --> 10:07.481
Why are you crying?

10:07.523 --> 10:09.066
Hmm?

10:12.612 --> 10:15.489
There's a price
        for everything, Dad.

10:16.532 --> 10:18.784
Well, maybe we already paid it.

10:19.577 --> 10:23.623
I know how impossible
           this all seems.

10:24.498 --> 10:25.958
But now there's this man...

10:25.958 --> 10:28.294
He's not
           just a man, Dad.

10:29.545 --> 10:30.755
I know.

10:33.507 --> 10:36.177
He needs you to take him...

10:36.177 --> 10:38.679
Yeah, I'm not leaving
       you and Molly now, Dad.

10:38.721 --> 10:41.557
Now is exactly
         the time to leave.

10:41.599 --> 10:43.517
We don't know
         if it's real, or--

10:43.517 --> 10:45.019
It feels real.

10:45.603 --> 10:47.313
Real as anything.

10:48.689 --> 10:50.941
And even if it goes away,

10:50.983 --> 10:52.693
everything is different now.

10:54.487 --> 10:56.322
It's still you and me, Dad.

11:01.827 --> 11:04.705
You and me
      have been twisted around

11:04.705 --> 11:06.540
a couple of times already.

11:11.128 --> 11:13.589
I should never
         have let it happen.

11:13.631 --> 11:15.424
What does that mean?

11:15.424 --> 11:16.801
You think you owe me.

11:16.801 --> 11:18.260
-Oh, I do.
                -No.

11:18.302 --> 11:19.679
-I do--
                -No!

11:20.680 --> 11:22.348
But I let you think that.

11:23.432 --> 11:25.768
You think your penance
        for what has happened

11:25.768 --> 11:27.520
is for you to quash your light

11:27.561 --> 11:30.064
because it's been
         blinding sometimes.

11:30.523 --> 11:31.816
No one...

11:32.441 --> 11:34.360
No one would ever

11:34.360 --> 11:38.739
want you to close the doors
            on your mind.

11:42.993 --> 11:45.162
Now there's a door
          in front of you.

11:45.204 --> 11:50.167
On the other side is something
       I could never imagine.

11:51.752 --> 11:53.379
And this man...

11:56.716 --> 11:59.719
This man came to you for help.

12:00.553 --> 12:05.224
How could you possibly deny
    yourself this next step, huh?

12:06.434 --> 12:07.935
You would lose your mind,

12:07.935 --> 12:11.397
and I will not be your excuse.

12:14.817 --> 12:16.610
I don't want you here
             any longer.

12:16.652 --> 12:18.571
Not a minute,
         do you understand?

12:18.738 --> 12:19.780
Hmm?

12:22.658 --> 12:24.243
Molly will be fine.

12:27.329 --> 12:28.539
Look at me.

12:29.707 --> 12:30.875
Hmm?

12:32.960 --> 12:35.296
Come. Come.

12:58.444 --> 12:59.779
One groove.

13:10.915 --> 13:13.292
I want to give you a gift.

13:18.839 --> 13:22.885
My mother, Alma,
     made me a presentable man.

13:22.927 --> 13:27.181
Now, you are traveling across
    the country with my daughter.

13:31.018 --> 13:34.647
We are going to have to
          tighten this up.

13:39.985 --> 13:41.821
Gotta keep it tight.

13:41.862 --> 13:43.113
See? Tight.

13:47.785 --> 13:49.078
I'll only be gone
          a few days, okay?

13:49.078 --> 13:52.790
Mom! Get out of the house,
      you drive everyone crazy.

13:52.790 --> 13:54.124
You've been cast out.

13:54.124 --> 13:56.085
Please, baby Jesus,
            cast her out!

13:56.126 --> 13:57.002
Molly, Molly, Molly.

13:57.044 --> 13:59.129
I need to speak to you
           about Grandpa.

13:59.129 --> 14:01.966
Yeah, yeah. Grandpa's cured.
        Grandpa's all better!

14:02.007 --> 14:04.510
He said he took like
     a hundred million medicines

14:04.552 --> 14:08.097
and this morning's medicine
    was the one that achieved...

14:08.097 --> 14:09.598
-Mass.
              -...mass.

14:09.598 --> 14:10.891
'Cause that's science.

14:10.933 --> 14:12.017
And we're gonna make Eggos.

14:12.059 --> 14:13.686
-And pancakes!
           -And pancakes.

14:13.686 --> 14:16.063
All by ourselves!

14:16.105 --> 14:17.690
-So...
             -On one...

14:17.731 --> 14:18.899
Bye!

14:29.243 --> 14:30.786
He looks regular.

14:30.828 --> 14:32.538
funk music continues playing

15:19.043 --> 15:20.502
music stops

15:20.544 --> 15:22.046
What did you do

15:22.880 --> 15:23.964
to my dad?

15:23.964 --> 15:25.591
I realigned him.

15:26.425 --> 15:28.886
How long will he be
           like he is now?

15:28.886 --> 15:30.596
The rest of his life.

15:35.726 --> 15:36.894
I...

15:38.062 --> 15:39.438
I just...

15:42.107 --> 15:43.150
Thank you.

15:43.150 --> 15:46.820
A temporary solution is not
          a solution, boo.

15:46.862 --> 15:47.947
Boo?

15:48.739 --> 15:50.449
No. 

15:50.783 --> 15:51.742
None of that.

15:51.784 --> 15:55.371
You know, you say things
   without understanding context.

15:55.412 --> 15:57.998
That seems to be
         the strategy here.

15:58.040 --> 16:00.960
The misperception regarding
    communication on this planet

16:00.960 --> 16:03.712
is the illusion
      that it has taken place.

16:03.712 --> 16:04.838
Stop it.

16:05.089 --> 16:06.173
Okay.

16:06.173 --> 16:07.925
You have to tell me the plan.

16:09.301 --> 16:10.511
In the vaults of OriGen

16:10.511 --> 16:13.097
is Thomas Newton's tenth design.

16:13.097 --> 16:14.765
He failed to build it.

16:14.807 --> 16:17.518
We have to build it.

16:17.518 --> 16:20.270
Tenth design?
       You said it was fusion.

16:20.312 --> 16:21.480
Your dissertation theorized

16:21.480 --> 16:23.399
the possibility of fusing
            atomic nuclei

16:23.440 --> 16:26.068
by combining magnetic field
      containment with plasma--

16:26.068 --> 16:27.236
No, no, no, no. There's no way

16:27.236 --> 16:28.946
of reaching the kind of
      temperatures you'd need.

16:28.946 --> 16:30.072
And even if you could,

16:30.072 --> 16:31.365
there's still way
         too many questions

16:31.365 --> 16:33.075
about breeding enough tritium.

16:33.117 --> 16:34.618
Drive over there.

17:00.978 --> 17:02.312
It's dead.

17:22.124 --> 17:23.709
-Are you all right?

17:26.879 --> 17:30.507
Uh...
         Are you all right?

18:16.595 --> 18:18.972
There is no radioactivity.

18:25.229 --> 18:27.606
This is cold fusion?

18:27.731 --> 18:28.816
No.

18:28.857 --> 18:30.984
Quantum. Ta-da.

18:32.444 --> 18:34.947
How long will this
          pumpjack run for?

18:34.988 --> 18:36.281
-Decades.
        -How'd you scale it?

18:36.281 --> 18:38.408
I mean, this is
       generations ahead of--

18:38.408 --> 18:40.160
Centuries beyond
        human understanding.

18:40.202 --> 18:42.079
-An energy cell.
            -A prototype.

18:42.079 --> 18:43.205
-You built it?
                -No.

18:43.247 --> 18:45.415
Thomas Newton
         was the architect.

18:45.457 --> 18:46.625
I assembled the components.

18:46.625 --> 18:50.254
Totally clean?
       No radiation, no decay?

18:50.295 --> 18:53.465
But this prototype powered
          my journey here.

18:53.465 --> 18:55.134
It is nearly drained.

18:59.680 --> 19:03.976
The tenth design
     is for a regenerating cell.

19:04.643 --> 19:07.354
Inexhaustible. Limitless.

19:07.354 --> 19:11.316
It will restore Anthea's
          core temperature.

19:18.907 --> 19:20.159
Oh, my God.

19:21.910 --> 19:23.871
It's barely warm.

19:23.871 --> 19:26.039
Our sea is boiled.

19:26.039 --> 19:28.333
To achieve fusion, we need...

19:30.294 --> 19:31.670
Water.

19:33.338 --> 19:36.133
You... You came for water.

19:36.550 --> 19:39.511
Earth is on the same trajectory,

19:39.553 --> 19:41.513
facing the same collapse.

19:41.513 --> 19:44.224
You know this.
         It is in your work.

19:44.266 --> 19:46.226
I could've never imagined this.

19:46.226 --> 19:48.187
You did imagine.

19:48.228 --> 19:51.565
You came closer than anyone
          in human history.

19:51.607 --> 19:53.192
And when you couldn't continue,

19:53.233 --> 19:55.235
you still chose to work

19:55.235 --> 19:58.030
as a caretaker of the planet.

20:05.454 --> 20:06.455
Where are you going?

20:06.455 --> 20:08.415
Yeah. I just...
          I need a minute.

20:08.415 --> 20:09.666
We have to get to--

20:09.708 --> 20:11.585
Please,
        I just need a minute.

21:34.418 --> 21:35.711
Dr. Gregory Papel,

21:35.752 --> 21:40.173
Icarus Program. Date is
         September 14th, 1984.

21:40.173 --> 21:41.675
0300 hours.

21:41.675 --> 21:45.554
Subject refuses to reveal
      algorithm for tenth design.

21:45.554 --> 21:48.056
Ongoing dehydration protocol

21:48.056 --> 21:50.017
largely ineffective.

21:51.685 --> 21:53.103
You're bleeding!

21:53.145 --> 21:54.604
Don't you see it?

21:54.646 --> 21:57.566
Your blood,
        your children's blood.

21:57.566 --> 22:00.861
You are so careless!

22:00.902 --> 22:03.030
Will you get
         Mr. Newton some gin?

22:03.030 --> 22:04.364
Yes.

22:04.364 --> 22:06.575
Yes.

22:06.616 --> 22:07.993
More.  

22:08.327 --> 22:09.036
More.

22:09.077 --> 22:12.998
I don't want to
            set the world

22:13.332 --> 22:17.544
On fire

22:17.586 --> 22:22.382
I just want to start

22:22.382 --> 22:25.344
A flame in your heart

22:25.385 --> 22:26.678
No X-ray!

22:26.678 --> 22:29.514
No, no, no. No. Not my eyes!

22:29.556 --> 22:33.477
-Not my eyes!

22:36.980 --> 22:37.773
Ah.

22:37.814 --> 22:42.027
I can't see.
             I can't see.

22:42.569 --> 22:44.196
Please help me.

22:44.571 --> 22:46.490
Mary Lou...

22:46.531 --> 22:49.659
I just wanna go home.

22:49.701 --> 22:52.537
Mary Lou. Mary Lou...

22:58.377 --> 23:02.547
I just want to be
          the one you love

23:09.137 --> 23:13.141
I'll have reached the goal
           I'm dreaming of

23:13.183 --> 23:14.810
Believe me

23:14.851 --> 23:20.357
I don't want to
        set the world on fire

23:24.653 --> 23:29.616
I just want to start

23:29.616 --> 23:34.913
A flame in your heart

23:39.167 --> 23:40.293
Mom,

23:40.293 --> 23:41.628
Grandpa said I don't have to
            brush my teeth.

23:41.628 --> 23:44.172
-Don't tell her.
   -And we bought Skittles

23:44.214 --> 23:45.966
and ate 'em for dinner.

23:45.966 --> 23:47.717
-Miss Molly!
    -And then we watched

23:47.717 --> 23:49.094
cricket until 18.

23:49.094 --> 23:51.263
Juzzie,
          everything is fine.

23:51.304 --> 23:53.223
We love you, goodbye.

24:24.296 --> 24:25.630
The stars

24:26.214 --> 24:31.136
look very different from here.

24:32.095 --> 24:33.180
Yeah.

24:35.223 --> 24:36.933
Yeah, I'll say.

24:42.272 --> 24:43.982
Is it time to leave?

24:44.149 --> 24:45.275
No.

24:46.109 --> 24:50.155
We have, uh,
        something to discuss.

24:56.244 --> 24:58.497
What was it like on Anthea?

24:59.539 --> 25:00.665
Before.

25:03.585 --> 25:05.170
When I was a pupa,

25:07.631 --> 25:11.343
the sea was
        already disappearing.

25:13.428 --> 25:15.347
The fauna was toxic.

25:16.598 --> 25:19.518
Herd animals were dying.

25:20.519 --> 25:22.521
How many of you are left?

25:25.190 --> 25:27.400
Only a few thousand.

25:27.442 --> 25:31.363
There are still some
         at the pupal stage.

25:33.907 --> 25:36.159
I'm so sorry.

25:42.582 --> 25:45.585
How long do we have here?

25:45.585 --> 25:49.256
The domino has already tipped.

25:50.006 --> 25:54.344
As a species, you have chosen
       to ignore the symptoms.

25:54.386 --> 25:55.720
How long?

25:56.513 --> 25:58.598
By 2030,

25:59.766 --> 26:02.602
temperatures will have risen

26:02.602 --> 26:05.397
above your extinction threshold.

26:06.189 --> 26:08.149
From there,
        the remaining dominos

26:08.149 --> 26:10.569
will fall in a matter
             of decades.

26:15.657 --> 26:17.200
2030.

26:22.872 --> 26:24.541
I don't know
        if you're right about

26:24.583 --> 26:27.085
why I was working
         like I was working.

26:28.795 --> 26:30.422
I just...

26:31.965 --> 26:34.050
The work was like breathing.

26:34.092 --> 26:37.429
-It felt...
            -Inevitable.

26:38.263 --> 26:39.598
Yeah.

26:40.890 --> 26:45.228
But it was destructive
             to others.

26:45.604 --> 26:48.565
If you destroyed nothing,

26:48.607 --> 26:52.193
you would have
        accomplished nothing.

26:52.235 --> 26:56.156
What I accomplished
     wasn't worth what was lost.

26:56.656 --> 26:58.491
By what scale?

26:59.701 --> 27:02.787
Well, it's not so simple
       to answer that question

27:02.787 --> 27:05.665
now I've understood
   I'm not alone in the universe.

27:06.541 --> 27:09.127
With the spaceman

27:09.794 --> 27:11.880
and blue cubes
       from other dimensions,

27:11.921 --> 27:13.757
thank you very much.

27:13.798 --> 27:16.134
So are you a scientist...

27:17.552 --> 27:19.804
or are you
         something else now?

27:22.641 --> 27:23.683
Take...

27:24.267 --> 27:26.770
Take what you need
           back with you,

27:27.854 --> 27:30.357
but leave the blueprint here.

27:30.357 --> 27:34.152
Give us the same chance
    to fix ourselves as you have.

27:36.029 --> 27:37.364
That's the deal.

27:38.365 --> 27:39.658
If I agree,

27:41.034 --> 27:44.162
you will agree to be
         a scientist again.

27:47.624 --> 27:49.334
Yes.

27:50.877 --> 27:52.796
Yeah, I will

27:53.588 --> 27:55.715
agree to be a scientist again.

27:56.716 --> 27:58.510
When I am gone,

28:00.095 --> 28:02.847
you can keep the design.

28:10.772 --> 28:13.233
How do you plan on getting back?

28:14.484 --> 28:16.695
Newton will inform me

28:17.779 --> 28:19.698
when it's time.

28:19.698 --> 28:22.409
How are we supposed
        to get inside OriGen?

28:22.450 --> 28:26.413
Newton instructed me to find

28:27.372 --> 28:29.499
the Wizard of Risk.

28:29.874 --> 28:32.752
-Is that a game?
                -No.

28:34.921 --> 28:36.673
It's a person.

28:43.221 --> 28:44.973
Please. I just need
         a little more time.

28:45.014 --> 28:47.434
I needed someone who could
       get me into Book Club!

28:47.475 --> 28:49.811
Okay? You said you could
       do that for me, Hatch.

28:49.853 --> 28:50.937
I said I could try.

28:50.979 --> 28:52.355
I said I would make some calls.

28:52.355 --> 28:53.773
Well, Book Club's
         this fucking week!

28:53.815 --> 28:54.899
Look, your app isn't ready,

28:54.941 --> 28:56.901
it violates about
       a million privacy laws.

28:56.901 --> 28:58.111
-Not that privacy exists.
         -Oh, it's perfect.

28:58.153 --> 29:00.405
So what? I'm supposed to wait
          until next year?

29:00.405 --> 29:01.948
Fuck me? Well, fuck you!

29:01.990 --> 29:04.868
You can wait till next year
          before I pay you.

29:04.909 --> 29:05.869
All right. You know what?

29:05.869 --> 29:07.078
Your app's a piece
           of shit anyway.

29:07.078 --> 29:08.621
--I wouldn't wipe my ass with it.

29:08.663 --> 29:09.998
You wanna get rich?

29:10.039 --> 29:11.916
Invent an app
        that can wipe my ass.

29:11.958 --> 29:15.253
And go through puberty.
          What are you, 11?

29:24.596 --> 29:26.473
-Hatch Flood?
               -Jesus.

29:26.514 --> 29:29.934
Uh, to my intense regret, yeah.

29:29.976 --> 29:32.312
-You okay?
   -I have shingles. Who are you?

29:32.312 --> 29:35.356
My name is Justin Falls,
        this is Mr. Faraday,

29:35.398 --> 29:38.026
and your office told us
       you'd probably be here.

29:38.067 --> 29:40.278
-What do you want?
          -An IP attorney.

29:42.739 --> 29:44.282
You are the Wizard.

29:44.324 --> 29:46.493
-Where is your hat?
       -Put that away.

29:46.493 --> 29:49.996
-This is you.
    -Yeah, I was blackout drunk.

29:49.996 --> 29:53.166
But it is on the Internet.
          You chose a font.

29:53.166 --> 29:55.376
Have you ever made a sex tape?

29:55.418 --> 29:56.753
All right.
      Well, that's mine, okay?

29:56.753 --> 29:58.087
And it has a font.
          What do you want?

29:58.129 --> 30:01.800
I was instructed to harness
      your rage against OriGen.

30:02.675 --> 30:03.802
That's not funny.

30:13.019 --> 30:15.480
-It's an algorithm--
         -I know what it is.

30:16.356 --> 30:19.943
You remember the times
          you see base 60.

30:21.319 --> 30:23.988
-How did you get this?
            -He wrote it.

30:24.030 --> 30:25.532
Bullshit.

30:25.532 --> 30:26.950
How did you...

30:27.659 --> 30:28.409
I don't...

30:28.409 --> 30:30.036
You know what?
         I don't wanna know.

30:30.078 --> 30:33.998
Thomas Jerome Newton
        sent me to find you.

30:35.792 --> 30:37.001
Thomas Newton

30:37.544 --> 30:38.837
sent you to me.

30:38.878 --> 30:39.963
I just said that.

30:39.963 --> 30:41.339
What else did Newton
           say about him?

30:41.381 --> 30:43.883
-He said that he--
       -No, no, no. Tell him.

30:43.925 --> 30:46.469
He said
      that you had a good nose,

30:46.469 --> 30:51.015
but the only one
       you could not sniff out

30:51.516 --> 30:52.851
was you.

30:55.186 --> 30:57.355
Keep the fuck away from me.

30:59.732 --> 31:02.443
-You need to come with us.
    -Get the fuck out of the way!

31:02.485 --> 31:04.946
-And stay away from me.
        -All right.

31:04.946 --> 31:07.115
We're at the Holiday Inn
              on Aurora

31:07.156 --> 31:09.534
if you change your mind.
             All right?

31:39.439 --> 31:41.190
You had
        no idea what it was.

31:41.232 --> 31:43.484
Spencer, how the hell
      would I know what it was?

31:43.484 --> 31:46.362
Let's just put a pin
   in the spaceman part for a sec.

31:46.362 --> 31:48.281
"A pin in
         the spaceman part"?

31:48.323 --> 31:50.742
-Oh, okay.
          -Just follow me.

31:50.742 --> 31:53.786
1975, Thomas Newton,
            he comes here

31:53.786 --> 31:55.204
and he makes a fortune off

31:55.246 --> 31:56.247
nine patents that he uses

31:56.247 --> 31:57.624
to start a company
      called World Enterprises.

31:57.665 --> 32:01.419
Okay? And then he leads
   the tech industry for a decade.

32:01.836 --> 32:02.879
Until we grab him.

32:02.921 --> 32:04.213
We annex the company,
            we box it up,

32:04.213 --> 32:05.214
we ship it off to the UK

32:05.214 --> 32:07.050
to avoid
   congressional oversight, right?

32:07.050 --> 32:09.510
Then we fold it into
    a British industrial supplier

32:09.510 --> 32:12.430
called OriGen, uh,
       run by an Edward Flood.

32:12.430 --> 32:15.808
And meanwhile,
       Newton just disappears.

32:15.850 --> 32:17.393
What do you mean, "disappears"?

32:17.435 --> 32:19.020
During the interrogation,

32:19.020 --> 32:21.105
he revealed a tenth patent
        that he never built.

32:21.147 --> 32:23.316
Okay. He wouldn't
       give it all the way up.

32:23.358 --> 32:25.026
Cryptography couldn't crack it.

32:25.026 --> 32:26.778
And it was written in base 60.

32:26.819 --> 32:28.988
Stop, Spencer. What is that?

32:28.988 --> 32:32.241
It's a form of arithmetic last
      used by the Mesopotamians

32:32.241 --> 32:34.619
3,600 years before Christ.

32:34.661 --> 32:37.163
It's symbols, Drew, okay?

32:37.205 --> 32:38.957
And the most recurrent
         in Newton's patent

32:38.998 --> 32:42.168
is a sun motif,
      which leads me to believe

32:42.210 --> 32:44.837
it's a design for
     some kind of energy source.

32:48.758 --> 32:49.801
Okay.

32:52.470 --> 32:55.765
So now there's another visitor

32:56.140 --> 32:57.141
and the two of them are--

32:57.141 --> 32:58.643
We don't know
      what they're doing. Okay?

32:58.685 --> 33:00.311
All we know is that
        there is a blueprint

33:00.353 --> 33:02.146
for a power source
      from outer fucking space

33:02.188 --> 33:04.315
sitting in the OriGen vault
   and Newton's still in the wind.

33:04.357 --> 33:06.526
Spencer, you know
    what I have to ask you here.

33:06.526 --> 33:10.154
I know that my own psych map
          inclines me to--

33:10.154 --> 33:12.156
The white whale obsession.

33:12.198 --> 33:15.952
Yeah, I was gonna say
         hyper focus but...

33:17.620 --> 33:19.330
It doesn't mean
     I'm off the mark, you know?

33:19.330 --> 33:21.290
It means it could be
         dangerous for you.

33:21.332 --> 33:23.001
Listen to me.
        Listen to me, please.

33:23.001 --> 33:25.461
I know what this is
         activating in you.

33:25.461 --> 33:29.007
You'll never find the first
      eight years of your life

33:29.007 --> 33:31.801
because there's nothing there.

33:31.801 --> 33:33.011
If I hadn't stopped you,

33:33.052 --> 33:36.806
you would've searched forever
       and died empty-handed.

33:36.806 --> 33:38.224
I know you want me safe.

33:38.266 --> 33:41.019
Safe and optimal.

33:41.060 --> 33:43.855
Fuck. I put a lot of effort
              into you.

33:43.896 --> 33:45.898
That patent could be
          a recipe for dip.

33:45.940 --> 33:47.358
Oh, it's not fucking dip, Drew.

33:47.400 --> 33:50.194
Everyone involved
     in the original op is dead.

33:50.194 --> 33:52.321
Of course. It's been 45 years.

33:52.321 --> 33:53.448
After talking to Papel,
           there's no way

33:53.448 --> 33:55.033
I'm gonna believe
    they all died in their sleep.

33:55.074 --> 33:57.035
You got to trust me on this.

34:03.207 --> 34:07.045
Spencer, I can't
         compute "spaceman."

34:08.379 --> 34:10.757
But I can compute
         "everybody's dead."

34:10.798 --> 34:14.510
Because we do that when there's
    something worth killing for.

34:20.183 --> 34:23.227
I want to run this, okay?

34:24.187 --> 34:25.646
I want the resources.

34:25.688 --> 34:27.982
I want the clearances.
    You just got to put me on it.

34:28.024 --> 34:30.068
Let me find the new one.
           I'll find him.

34:30.068 --> 34:34.072
I will find him
      and I will bring him in.

34:34.072 --> 34:36.115
I always do, you know.

34:40.078 --> 34:41.204
Find him.

34:41.204 --> 34:43.664
But you let him run
            a little bit.

34:43.664 --> 34:44.749
Yeah.

34:45.374 --> 34:47.877
If that tenth design
            is a weapon,

34:48.461 --> 34:50.630
maybe it can be our weapon.

34:52.048 --> 34:53.299
How much do you need?

34:53.299 --> 34:55.343
Half a million for
       surveillance build-out,

34:55.384 --> 34:58.221
and a person to help me
     with intel. That'd be good.

34:58.221 --> 35:00.723
Oh. Somebody in mind?

35:00.765 --> 35:02.433
Yeah, um...

35:02.433 --> 35:06.020
Your analyst who first
         detected the signal

35:06.020 --> 35:08.106
in New Mexico,
          her background is

35:09.023 --> 35:10.775
very interesting.

35:11.067 --> 35:12.110
Hmm?

35:14.487 --> 35:16.114
I'll be nice.

36:26.350 --> 36:28.311
I know of one other person

36:28.352 --> 36:30.354
who understood base 60,

36:30.396 --> 36:32.982
let alone calculated in it.

36:33.024 --> 36:34.734
And I have a nightmarish,

36:34.734 --> 36:38.738
crazy-making idea about
         where he was from.

36:38.738 --> 36:40.698
So I need to know
          where he's from,

36:40.740 --> 36:43.242
and I need to know
        what he's doing here.

36:44.285 --> 36:47.079
And please, God,
          don't lie to me.

36:55.254 --> 36:57.089
Come on in.

37:07.642 --> 37:10.978
Hatch?
            Hey, come on.

37:11.020 --> 37:12.480
You passed out.

37:12.521 --> 37:14.398
Hey, hey. Are you okay?

37:14.398 --> 37:16.442
-Can you sit up?

37:16.442 --> 37:19.737
Here you go.
          Have some water.

37:22.365 --> 37:24.116
Are you afraid of me?

37:27.870 --> 37:28.955
Yes.

37:30.122 --> 37:33.417
The message is
          "Mars needs women."

37:34.252 --> 37:36.212
"Mars needs women."

37:37.421 --> 37:38.673
He's been watching TCM.

37:38.673 --> 37:41.550
Look, I know that you
        must have questions,

37:41.592 --> 37:43.094
-so...
   -Yeah, I have a bunch.

37:44.553 --> 37:46.430
-He's from--
              -Anthea.

37:48.140 --> 37:49.934
And he brought cold fusion.

37:49.934 --> 37:51.060
Quantum.

37:51.060 --> 37:52.979
That's the tenth design?

37:54.313 --> 37:56.107
Does OriGen know what they have?

37:56.148 --> 37:59.277
No. Nobody could figure it out.

37:59.527 --> 38:00.861
Jesus.

38:00.903 --> 38:02.238
Fusion?

38:02.280 --> 38:03.531
Do you know
            what this is?

38:03.531 --> 38:05.199
I mean, do you know
          what this means?

38:05.241 --> 38:06.534
Why are you whispering?

38:06.534 --> 38:08.619
Because I'm fucking terrified.

38:08.619 --> 38:09.578
Okay, I do risk.

38:09.620 --> 38:11.872
I hedge against very real,
          very bad things.

38:11.914 --> 38:13.582
Okay. And you're talking
          about liberating

38:13.582 --> 38:15.876
the planet Earth
          from oil forever.

38:15.876 --> 38:17.878
Do you know
        what that looks like?

38:17.878 --> 38:20.798
In the first 30 days,
       the exchanges collapse.

38:20.798 --> 38:23.009
Nobody has any security
           from anything.

38:23.050 --> 38:24.302
Policing is gone.

38:24.343 --> 38:25.970
People are jumping off
            of buildings.

38:25.970 --> 38:29.307
It makes 1929 look like
         fucking Christmas.

38:29.307 --> 38:32.601
It's an addicted planet
         going cold turkey.

38:32.601 --> 38:34.103
There's lots of riots.

38:34.103 --> 38:35.896
Power grids go obsolete.

38:35.938 --> 38:37.940
I mean, a massive
        devaluation of land.

38:37.982 --> 38:41.986
I mean, I could buy a fucking
     747 for two Pokemon cards.

38:42.028 --> 38:43.863
Millions of people are
        gonna lose their jobs

38:43.863 --> 38:45.990
in the gas and oil sector alone.

38:45.990 --> 38:47.950
Governments slash funding
           to everything.

38:47.950 --> 38:49.869
Okay. Everybody withdraws
    their troops from everywhere,

38:49.869 --> 38:51.203
because there's nothing left
            to fight for.

38:51.245 --> 38:53.372
Until they decide to train their
    weapons on their own citizens

38:53.372 --> 38:55.291
for begging for food and water

38:55.291 --> 38:56.500
and medicine
        and humanitarian aid.

38:56.542 --> 38:59.337
And hey, if you're in
   the cardboard coffin business,

38:59.378 --> 39:01.380
it'll be a fucking bonanza.

39:01.422 --> 39:04.467
Iraq, Bolivia, Norway are done.

39:04.467 --> 39:07.053
China, Germany,
         France are better.

39:07.094 --> 39:08.846
Nobody gives a shit about
         the Saudis anymore,

39:08.846 --> 39:11.349
so we just redraw the map
          of Central Asia.

39:11.349 --> 39:13.768
Africa. The entire
        continent of Africa.

39:13.768 --> 39:15.436
They've got the minerals,
        the infrastructure...

39:15.478 --> 39:16.812
I can't, I can't...

39:16.812 --> 39:19.315
-I... I've gotta go.

39:25.154 --> 39:27.656
Hey! Hey. Hey, hey, hey.

39:27.698 --> 39:29.575
-Ah! Shingles.
         -Oh, I'm so sorry.

39:29.575 --> 39:31.619
Look, fusion declares war
           on everything.

39:31.619 --> 39:33.746
And everything is gonna
         declare war on us.

39:33.746 --> 39:35.915
If we don't,
         we're done by 2030.

39:35.915 --> 39:38.459
2030? Where did you get that?

39:38.501 --> 39:40.336
I can't hedge chaos.

39:40.336 --> 39:43.172
Chaos is why humans exist.

39:43.172 --> 39:45.216
Meteors and dinosaurs.

39:45.216 --> 39:47.385
Shifting land masses.

39:47.385 --> 39:49.512
Eclipses, plague, war.

39:49.553 --> 39:51.514
You rise and you adapt.

39:51.555 --> 39:55.267
You regrow your brains
           and you adapt.

39:55.309 --> 39:59.230
This is the next step,
             Mr. Flood.

39:59.480 --> 40:01.065
When we take it...

40:01.774 --> 40:05.569
nothing will ever be the same.

40:15.496 --> 40:16.789
I'm Spencer Clay,
           Miss Dominguez.

40:16.831 --> 40:19.875
-Come in. -Oh, okay.

40:19.917 --> 40:22.545
I'm sorry, I thought we were
      meeting half an hour ago.

40:22.586 --> 40:24.505
Did I get the time wrong?

40:24.547 --> 40:26.257
No. 

40:26.298 --> 40:27.716
No, you didn't.

40:27.758 --> 40:28.843
Pleased to meet you, sir.

40:28.884 --> 40:30.928
You're doing well
           in SIGINT, huh?

40:31.220 --> 40:32.096
Thank you, sir.

40:32.096 --> 40:33.764
Do you know why
        I wanted to meet you?

40:33.806 --> 40:35.933
I did not invite you to sit.

40:37.143 --> 40:39.603
Now I'm just wondering
         about your accent.

40:39.603 --> 40:41.313
You didn't do the work
          to get rid of it.

40:41.313 --> 40:43.274
It's either arrogant or dumb.

40:43.315 --> 40:45.401
Let's hope it's the former.

40:45.443 --> 40:47.778
Five days ago,
      you intercepted a signal

40:47.820 --> 40:50.239
out of New Mexico coming
       from inside a tornado.

40:50.281 --> 40:50.990
Yes, sir.

40:51.031 --> 40:52.366
Did you discuss that
            with anyone?

40:52.366 --> 40:53.492
Of course not.

40:53.534 --> 40:54.493
Okay. Findings?

40:54.535 --> 40:56.620
The tornado was
     spinning counter clockwise.

40:56.662 --> 40:58.956
Only around 5% do that,

40:58.998 --> 41:01.667
and none ever reported
           in New Mexico.

41:01.667 --> 41:04.253
And what does
           that tell you?

41:05.004 --> 41:07.381
The frequency of that signal

41:07.423 --> 41:09.925
correlates to nothing on Earth.

41:10.759 --> 41:13.304
Lisa Elizabeth Dominguez.

41:13.345 --> 41:14.805
ROTC at 18.

41:14.847 --> 41:18.100
Tours, running signals
            in Islamabad.

41:19.268 --> 41:20.311
Sit.

41:20.352 --> 41:22.563
Oh. So this is interesting.

41:22.563 --> 41:24.732
Your parents immigrated
       from Portugal legally.

41:24.732 --> 41:27.276
Your uncle
       and his family did not.

41:27.276 --> 41:27.985
Correct.

41:28.027 --> 41:29.945
So you turned them over to ICE.

41:29.987 --> 41:31.655
My uncle thought
      he could game the system

41:31.655 --> 41:32.823
while my parents
         did the right thing

41:32.823 --> 41:34.783
and earned their way
         into this country.

41:34.783 --> 41:36.869
You could have just left
          your uncle alone,

41:36.911 --> 41:40.331
but what you did
          was... punitive.

41:40.831 --> 41:43.417
One could say
         the same about you,

41:43.417 --> 41:48.088
sending that Ukrainian family to
   a detention facility in Abilene

41:48.130 --> 41:50.966
and their little boy
           died in a cage.

41:51.634 --> 41:54.011
I think he was nine?

41:56.514 --> 41:59.475
I'm running an op.
         Close hold. Funded.

41:59.475 --> 42:00.851
Never gonna give you
         the whole picture,

42:00.851 --> 42:02.394
but if you
       figure it out yourself,

42:02.394 --> 42:03.646
I'll know I made
          the right choice.

42:03.687 --> 42:04.980
You do what I tell you,

42:04.980 --> 42:09.318
when I tell you,
          and nothing else.

42:10.319 --> 42:11.612
Read this.

42:11.612 --> 42:13.614
Find me any living connection
           to the subject.

42:13.656 --> 42:17.034
Name's Thomas Jerome Newton.
          Help me find him,

42:17.076 --> 42:20.371
you can just write
      your own ticket... Lisa.

42:21.622 --> 42:23.499
Thank you, sir.

42:23.499 --> 42:25.793
I look forward
         to the opportunity.

42:25.793 --> 42:27.545
Well, all right.

42:29.838 --> 42:31.215
Oh, and, hey, Lise,

42:31.799 --> 42:33.509
now that we're gonna be
          working together,

42:33.551 --> 42:35.719
watch your fucking mouth.

42:43.394 --> 42:45.729
R&B music plays

42:49.858 --> 42:51.402
I got to ask.

42:51.402 --> 42:52.695
Your face is amazing.

42:52.736 --> 42:55.072
Is that a real face, huh?
             How is it--

42:55.114 --> 42:56.949
Did you make it?
          What's the deal?

42:56.991 --> 42:58.409
It's a skin suit.

42:58.409 --> 42:59.535
Oh, a skin suit?

42:59.535 --> 43:01.829
Skin suit. Skin suit.

43:01.870 --> 43:03.372
I do not understand.

43:03.414 --> 43:05.833
I was told OriGen
           was in Seattle.

43:05.833 --> 43:08.043
What's in Seattle is a phone
           and an office.

43:08.085 --> 43:09.587
OriGen proper is in London.

43:09.628 --> 43:11.755
London's the only
       top-five tech ecosystem

43:11.797 --> 43:13.340
with a startup visa program.

43:13.382 --> 43:16.677
So, the capital benefits
    outweigh even Silicon Valley.

43:16.677 --> 43:18.220
He really likes his hot sauce.

43:18.262 --> 43:21.432
I fled England in disgrace,
        if you're wondering.

43:21.473 --> 43:23.058
Do you have disgrace
           on your planet?

43:23.100 --> 43:24.977
No, but I can smell it.

43:24.977 --> 43:27.146
You can't
         drink that in here.

43:27.187 --> 43:28.606
Oh, it's okay.
          I'm an attorney.

43:28.606 --> 43:29.690
We are going to England.

43:29.732 --> 43:31.609
-No, we're not.
           -I have fusion.

43:31.609 --> 43:32.526
I have a family.

43:32.526 --> 43:34.612
You can collect them
       when we are at OriGen.

43:34.653 --> 43:35.946
I can't just leave my daughter.

43:35.988 --> 43:39.908
Your child has one possible
          habitable future.

43:41.827 --> 43:43.495
So do mine.

43:44.163 --> 43:46.665
I have shown you the prototype.

43:48.709 --> 43:52.046
Are you going to deny
         what you have seen?

43:52.087 --> 43:56.091
It's not that simple.
       Edie doesn't trust me.

43:56.091 --> 44:00.304
She believes that I tried to
        sell Newton's design.

44:00.346 --> 44:01.972
-Did you?
                -No.

44:02.014 --> 44:02.973
And don't ask me that again.

44:02.973 --> 44:05.184
How do we get
      your sister to trust you?

44:05.225 --> 44:08.646
Okay. Tell me
     more about your prototype.

44:08.687 --> 44:09.855
It is nearly capacitated.

44:09.897 --> 44:12.066
Okay. But it works?
      You could demonstrate it?

44:12.107 --> 44:13.692
Uh, demonstrate it where?

44:14.818 --> 44:15.736
Book Club.

44:15.778 --> 44:18.072
-The tech startup thing?
        -Yeah. Have you been?

44:18.072 --> 44:21.825
A recruiter came to me at UNM.
     No one would remember that.

44:21.825 --> 44:23.827
We are going to Book Club.

44:23.869 --> 44:25.871
Well, it starts in 36 hours.

44:25.871 --> 44:27.539
Uh, Edie always keeps a seat.

44:27.581 --> 44:29.792
I mean, we'd have to
         get him a passport.

44:29.792 --> 44:31.043
You need fingerprints.

44:31.085 --> 44:32.836
-He doesn't have any.
        -No X-rays.

44:32.836 --> 44:35.214
We require
     alternative transportation.

44:35.214 --> 44:36.924
Last time
       he was at the airport,

44:36.924 --> 44:38.759
he vomited water
         for, like, an hour.

44:38.759 --> 44:39.968
Oh, that's wonderful.

44:40.010 --> 44:41.970
Um, well, listen. Uh...

44:41.970 --> 44:45.015
Fuck, we could book
          a private plane.

44:45.015 --> 44:46.975
I know a guy
        who's got a timeshare

44:47.017 --> 44:49.144
who might take my call.

44:49.186 --> 44:51.980
Then we could change the
 flight plan once we're airborne.

44:52.022 --> 44:53.440
Blame it on engine trouble.

44:53.482 --> 44:56.485
Then we could land off-grid
        at the Isle of Mull,

44:56.485 --> 44:57.569
they don't have customs.

44:57.569 --> 45:00.823
Then we could rent a car to
   London, we'd probably make it.

45:04.827 --> 45:06.745
Nobody was moving.

45:11.417 --> 45:12.668
This costs like...

45:12.668 --> 45:14.586
Yeah,
         my every last dime.

45:14.628 --> 45:16.046
Yesterday,
       my life was different.

45:16.046 --> 45:19.049
-Boy, do I fucking hear you.
              -Uh-huh.

45:19.091 --> 45:20.175
Hello, sir, I'm Ashley.

45:20.217 --> 45:21.719
I'll be your
       flight attendant today.

45:21.719 --> 45:23.846
Will the cabin be pressurized?

45:24.430 --> 45:26.557
Uh... Yes. Of course, sir.

45:30.352 --> 45:31.395
Wow.

45:33.897 --> 45:35.482
Can I offer you
         something to drink?

45:35.524 --> 45:36.442
Water, champagne?

45:36.442 --> 45:39.111
Yeah. I'll have a double
        vodka tonic, please.

45:50.038 --> 45:51.915
What the fuck? Justin?

45:51.957 --> 45:53.751
Face. Face. Fucked-up face.

45:55.377 --> 45:57.171
Shit. Shit, shit.

45:57.212 --> 45:59.298
You... You have
           to stay seated!

45:59.339 --> 46:01.675
-What's happening to his face?
            -Uh, nothing.

46:01.717 --> 46:02.926
-Is he having a stroke?
                -No.

46:02.968 --> 46:05.012
It's a nut allergy, but don't
     worry, she has his EpiPen.

46:05.053 --> 46:05.929
So listen, Ashley...

46:05.971 --> 46:07.264
Your face is falling
           off your skull.

46:07.264 --> 46:11.018
Is this maximum velocity
          for the aircraft?

46:11.059 --> 46:12.728
I'm sure you've seen
    things on this plane before.

46:12.728 --> 46:13.812
You know, like,
         billionaire things

46:13.854 --> 46:15.230
and acts of human callousness
           and depravity.

46:15.272 --> 46:16.940
The company makes you sign
           an NDA, right?

46:16.982 --> 46:18.233
What the fuck is happening?

46:18.275 --> 46:21.820
I was not wearing my skin suit
        when I traveled here.

46:21.820 --> 46:22.905
I don't know.

46:22.905 --> 46:24.990
It's fucking falling off.
          Will it go back?

46:25.032 --> 46:26.950
--Unclear.

46:26.950 --> 46:28.410
Sir, you need to sit down!

46:28.410 --> 46:30.412
You need to stay in here
          and not come out.

46:30.412 --> 46:32.080
Unless you have a staple gun,
         then we'll be fine.

46:32.122 --> 46:33.373
I'll just get
        the chips and drinks,

46:33.373 --> 46:35.584
and don't worry.
        Have a great flight!

46:50.891 --> 46:52.684
Why don't you
     bring your head in the car

46:52.726 --> 46:54.645
so that it doesn't explode?

46:56.688 --> 46:58.315
Is it your first time in London?

46:58.357 --> 47:01.151
If anybody offers you
        jellied eels, say no.

47:01.193 --> 47:02.611
So we just walk in?

47:02.611 --> 47:03.529
Yeah. I mean,

47:03.570 --> 47:05.113
